                <p dir="ltr">Bandai Namco has announced a new mode called Deep of Night for Elden Ring Nightreign. Set to arrive September 11, it's meant to offer a more challenging experience for veteran players with stronger enemies to face.</p><p dir="ltr">Deep of Night was officially revealed on <a href="https://www.bandainamcoent.com/news/elden-ring-nightreign-deep-of-night-has-appeared">the Bandai Namco website</a>, after it was <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/elden-ring-nightreign-ranked-mode-could-be-coming-according-to-datamine/1100-6533778/">datamined as a possible ranked mode for Elden Ring Nightreign</a> earlier this month. The mode will see wins and losses "affecting the depth" of players in this high-difficulty mode. The post challenges people to beat Depth 3, while specifying that the fourth and fifth levels are actually an "endless battle for those seeking even greater thrills."</p>



    
